This Python sample code demonstrates how to familiarize the reader with the PixLab API. These samples make an eye mask, a mustache filter, draw text, crop and extract faces, encrypt an image and more. The API provides a way to process and analyze input media images or video content using the PixLab Rest service. It uses built-in HTTP capabilities for passing parameters and authentication that responds with standard HTTP response codes. It also allows you to process, transform and filter images from any programming language with machine vision and deep learning APIs. PixLab provides media storage with scalable and unified RESTful APIs for media analysis and processing tasks.
Category: Media, Analytics, Applications, Big Data, Content, Identity, Images, Machine Learning, Meme, Mobile, Recognition, Storage

This is Java sample code for the MasterCard Simplify Commerce Online Payments NVP API that demonstrates integration. The Simplify Commerce API is a secure platform to build payments into an app or website. It allows you to add PCI-compliant payment pages to a site, control the user experience, and all of the sensitive payments data is stored on Mastercard servers. Simplify Commerce provides a way to implement an all-in-one payment solution for websites, mobile apps and in-person.
Category: Credit Cards, Applications, Financial, Merchants, Payments, Platform-as-a-Service, Transactions

The Simplify Commerce API is a secure platform to build payments into an app or website and allows you to add PCI-compliant payment pages to a site, control the user experience, and all of the sensitive payments data is stored on Mastercard servers. Simplify Commerce provides a way to implement all-in-one payment solution for websites, mobile apps and in-person.
Category: Credit Cards, Applications, Financial, Merchants, Payments, Platform-as-a-Service, Transactions

Description: This Java sample shows how to store your customer’s card securely with Simplify Commerce for repeat transactions. It demonstrates how the tokenization of Simplify Commerce, substitutes card information with a non-sensitive and valueless token. Card tokenization allows a merchant to securely save a customers card details and then process payments without having to transmit the card details to their own servers. The Simplify Commerce API is a secure platform to build payments into an app or website and allows you to add PCI-compliant payment pages to a site, control the user experience, and all of the sensitive payments data is stored on Mastercard servers. Simplify Commerce provides a way to implement all-in-one payment solution for websites, mobile apps and in-person.
Category: Credit Cards, Applications, Financial, Merchants, Payments, Platform-as-a-Service, Transactions
